In order to computationally perform active learning, we use this upper bound. In other words, the practical problem of interest becomes mins1:|s1b| s0s1 . This problem is equivalent to the k-Center problem (also called min-max facility location problem) (Wolf, 2011). In the next section, we explain how we solve the k-Center problem in practice using a greedy approximation.

